---
description: Prefer single quotes for strings in JS/TS
globs: ["*.js", "*.ts", "*.jsx", "*.tsx"]
alwaysApply: true
---

- Use single quotes (`'`) for all string literals
- **Use double quotes when the string contains a single quote** (preferred over escaping)
- Use template literals (backticks) for string interpolation or multi-line strings
- Examples:
  - ✅ Good: `const name = 'foo';`
  - ✅ Good: `const withQuote = "It's working";` (double quotes when string contains single quote)
  - ✅ Good: `const interpolated = \`Hello ${name}\`;`
  - ❌ Bad: `const name = "foo";`
  - ❌ Bad: `const withQuote = 'It\\'s working';` (avoid escaping)
